The number of confirmed coronavirus cases in South Africa has risen to 402 as confirmed by the Health Minister, Dr Zweli Mkhize today (Monday, 23 March). This means that there has been an increase of 128 from yesterday’s announcement, with the Northern Cape confirming its first case. Mkhize said that President Cyril Ramaphosa will address the nation on measures to be taken to mitigate the impact of Covid-19. He added that the public will be provided further details and explanations on the results including the significant rise, the ongoing testing procedures and each provinces progress on contact tracing efforts. President Ramaphosa is expected to speak to the nation tonight at a time to be confirmed. ” At that time the President would have finalized measures to be undertaken to mitigate the impact of the virus to our people and the economy. ” said Jackson Mthembu, Minister in the Presidency